									<div class="post_tag"><i class="fa fa-tags"></i><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/1970s/" rel="tag">1970s</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/20th-century/" rel="tag">20th century</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/activism/" rel="tag">activism</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/dean-van-nguyen/" rel="tag">Dean Van Nguyen</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/doubleday/" rel="tag">Doubleday</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/hip-hop/" rel="tag">hip-hop</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/knopf-doubleday-publishing-group/" rel="tag">Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/new-york-city/" rel="tag">New York City</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/penguin-random-house/" rel="tag">Penguin Random House</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/social-movements/" rel="tag">social movements</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/the-bronx/" rel="tag">The Bronx</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/tupac/" rel="tag">Tupac</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/tupac-shakur/" rel="tag">Tupac Shakur</a><a href="https://lithub.com/tag/words-for-my-comrades-a-political-history-of-tupac-shakur/" rel="tag">Words for My Comrades: A Political History of Tupac Shakur</a></div>									
																		
