									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/deanvannguyen/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Author-Photo_Dean-Van-Nguyen_-c-Daragh-Soden-scaled-e1745822313142-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Author-Photo_Dean-Van-Nguyen_-c-Daragh-Soden-scaled-e1745822313142-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Dean Van Nguyen" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/deanvannguyen/">Dean Van Nguyen</a></h6>
										Dean Van Nguyen is a music journalist and cultural critic for <em>Pitchfork</em>, <em>The Guardian</em>, <em>Bandcamp Daily</em>, and <em>Jacobin</em>, among others. He is based in Dublin, Ireland.																			</div>
